ht we had plenty. We still managed to lose anyway and during the CR Methods of Madness came in and took the kill. Sure this is legal and entirely within their right but it shows no compassion at all on their part as I repeatedly asked for them to help or at least to let us have another go at it. I think I was might be more deserving for wasting that much of my life starting at the monitor with minimal sleep for some other cleric to just walk in and say hey, he's up! and get his piece so easily. Yeah yeah that's the way it goes sometimes but that doesn't mean its the right thing to do to a person who has devoted so much time to it. Well that didn't work and here I am a week after going through that hellish camp with nothing to show for it. That was my last free week that I had time to do this. So that basically means I'll never get my epic or at least not for a long long time. This is a huge disappointment, I'm still somewhat in shock and feel totally disgusting. So for any clerics who plan on a camp in the future don't. It's not worth it. Grats to the cleric who got that piece today, I hope you're as happy with it as I would have been.<br><br>Rikishi Lifesaver<br>60th Dwarven High Priest <p><IMG SRC=http://heinzdbzsite.homestead.com/files/ss2gohan.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugartegilsson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gart Egilsson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/10/02 4:13:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=445.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://pantheon.yale.edu/~bdiebold/images/Gart1.jpg WIDTH=6