r>Nobody likes how this Ragefire change is working out, but I don't know how guilds are supposed to work out a compromise.  If we didn't engage, another guild would have, and there were other guilds massing their forces.  If we had let Rikishi take a second attempt, we would have most likely had to assist him to ensure a sucessful battle (not doing any uber weinie wagging here, Rikishi just didn't have many people in the zone to assist him).  If we had told Rikishi he could have this one and we would take the next one, we would have trampled all over the cleric next in line, who has been helping Rikishi camp since Wednesday.  <br>I wish I had an answer, and I wish that I didn't have conflicting feelings of happiness and disappointment.  I don't know Rikishi that well, but I do know several of the people who were helping him camp Ragefire, and they are great folks.  I know the MoM cleric who got the drops is a great person, and I know that MoM is full of great people.  <br>Would anyone be willing to come up with some sort of rotation for Ragefire?  Something like the old planes bookings?  Sign up, when it's your turn you and your crew camp it, you have 1 hour from the time he's up until he's FFA.  It would be nice if it were to work, but it would only work until the first guild decided not to honor the system.<br>I don't know the solution, and I don't know that there is a solution.  Maybe move Ragefire back to SolB, at least then you had a dungeon full of mobs to buy you some time.<br>I know that MoM did nothing wrong, and I know that I did nothing wrong, yet I still feel terrible for Rikishi.<br><br>Arolpin <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uarolpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arolpin</A> at: 2/10/02 6:36:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ualtarasotterkin01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>altarasotterkin01</A></span><br> <span class=u