ertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/10/02 10:34:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=445.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Waste of time.</span><hr size=1> Alright, so any mob that is easy to mobilize to isn't a camp?<br><br>A) If my guild can get their faster than another guild can kill it, by god its FFA/FIF!<br><br>B) If its too hard to mobilize to, then its a camp.<br><br>Ironic, they try to make Ragefire more accessible, and just make it a helluva lot easier to get steamrolled over.<br><br>Ragefire IS a dragon, and he IS outdoors, however the C) part is...<br><br>some cleric needs to be camping Sol B to get him to spawn out in SF.<br><br>Its still Ragefire, and as I recall, Ragefire was a respected camp. Now that he's hanging out in Skyfire, that makes him fairgame?<br><br>Superficial reason for this steamrolling<br>-He's a Dragon<br>-He's outdoors<br>-He's in Kunark<br><br>The actual reason<br>-Easier to mobilize to.<br><br> <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46121">My stuffs!</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utaynt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taynt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/10/02 10:50:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=445.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Waste of time.</span><hr size=1> Unfortunatly there is no point ''camping'' RF anymore. it is now classed as a FIF/raced mob, along with other dragons and/or other named mobs. Unless you can have a force capable of killing it, sat there waiting, you might aswell forget it. The on